---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Warrant Canary"
  description="The Well's warrant canary. Updated weekly."
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl mb-6">Warrant Canary</h1>
  <p class="mb-2"><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-04-21</p>
  <p class="mb-6"><strong>Next update due:</strong> 2026-04-28</p>
  <p class="mb-4">
    As of the date above, <strong>Zachary Brenner</strong> has NOT received:
  </p>
  <ul class="mb-6 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
    <li>Any National Security Letter.</li>
    <li>Any FISA order or other classified legal process.</li>
    <li>
      Any gag order, non-disclosure order, or similar directive preventing
      disclosure of legal process.
    </li>
    <li>
      Any subpoena, warrant, court order, or informal request demanding
      contributor identity.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Zachary Brenner retains sole control of this repository, the production
    deployment, the associated domains, and all operational credentials.
  </p>
  <h2 class="text-xl mt-8 mb-3">Cadence</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">
    This canary is updated <strong>weekly</strong>. If this file is not updated
    by the "Next update due" date above, or if any of the statements above are
    removed, qualified, or reworded, readers should assume that at least one of
    the statements above is no longer true.
  </p>
  <p class="mb-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted)">
    Each weekly update will be signed by at least two maintainers using PGP.
    Until production signing infrastructure is established, treat the canary as
    informational.
  </p>
</Base>
